00:12.721 --> 00:15.641
Some of these places
I haven't been in 20 years.

00:16.265 --> 00:17.516
Just see it in my memory.

00:18.060 --> 00:19.650
But I don't know how it is.

00:20.604 --> 00:22.024
I'm a little curious myself.

00:24.107 --> 00:25.067
Let's start off--

00:25.609 --> 00:27.689
Would you like to see the dental office?

00:31.532 --> 00:34.452
<i>Dentistry is a very tough job.</i>
<i>A very tough job.</i>

00:36.370 --> 00:38.660
Well, I got the corner office here, guys.

00:39.248 --> 00:40.248
That is my office.

00:41.542 --> 00:45.132
Made a nice living out of it,
wound up with three dental offices.

00:46.630 --> 00:49.300
Uh, never bought a practice,
I started from scratch.

00:49.383 --> 00:50.973
Wound up with 12,000 patients.

00:52.344 --> 00:53.184
Uh...

00:53.554 --> 00:55.014
Yeah, it almost killed me.

00:59.184 --> 01:02.694
<i>I was a practicing dentist</i>
<i>with a drug problem.</i>

01:03.814 --> 01:06.234
<i>Great dentist with a drug problem.</i>

01:09.027 --> 01:13.317
<i>Getting sober took about nine years.</i>

01:15.325 --> 01:18.195
And do I blame, uh, Maskell?

01:18.662 --> 01:20.462
Yes, I do. Do I blame myself?

01:20.539 --> 01:21.499
Yes, I do.

01:28.922 --> 01:31.802
<i>I went to St. Clement's.</i>
<i>I believe I started in 1958...</i>

01:32.426 --> 01:33.756
<i>uh, in first grade.</i>

01:36.555 --> 01:39.305
<i>The summer</i>
<i>between my seventh and eighth grade...</i>

01:45.355 --> 01:46.315
<i>I was an altar boy.</i>

01:50.777 --> 01:53.487
<i>Masses back in those days,</i>
<i>in the summer, went six o'clock,</i>

01:53.572 --> 01:56.412
<i>seven o'clock, and eight o'clock,</i>
<i>Monday through Friday.</i>

01:58.368 --> 02:02.408
They had a lot of Masses
because the parish was a thriving parish.

02:03.624 --> 02:06.634
<i>So, I would sit, say, a six o'clock Mass</i>
<i>or a seven o'clock Mass,</i>

02:06.710 --> 02:09.300
<i>and I'd have to--</i>
<i>I'd ride my bicycle down.</i>

02:12.507 --> 02:15.007
<i>That's where I met Father Maskell</i>
<i>for the first time.</i>

02:16.595 --> 02:21.175
<i>Really got to-- </i> [stammers]
<i>Started to know the fellow.</i>

02:24.770 --> 02:29.610
By November of my eighth grade,
he was driving me home.

02:31.401 --> 02:33.361
<i>He'd say, "Put the bike in the trunk.</i>

02:33.445 --> 02:36.105
<i>I'm gonna drive you home."</i>
<i>And we'd stop for a snowball.</i>

02:39.284 --> 02:42.414
I was the golden boy, I could do no wrong.

02:45.749 --> 02:49.589
This is St. Clement's Church over here.
Father Maskell was associate pastor.

02:50.712 --> 02:52.172
Look, this was the classroom.

02:53.507 --> 02:56.087
Here was a classroom
for the seventh and eighth grade.

03:00.055 --> 03:02.715
<i>Father Maskell would come</i>
<i>into my classroom...</i>

03:03.975 --> 03:07.515
<i>and ask to talk to me,</i>
<i>and he'd want to see me up at the rectory.</i>

03:08.772 --> 03:09.772
We're running up here.

03:10.273 --> 03:12.943
This is the-- The old rectory.

03:14.569 --> 03:16.779
<i>And at first,</i>
<i>it might have been once a week...</i>

03:17.447 --> 03:20.737
then it got to be where it was like
two, three, uh, times a week.

03:21.243 --> 03:26.123
And a lot of times I--
From lunch until the day ended,

03:26.873 --> 03:30.133
which I think was like 2:30,
I wouldn't be back in class.

03:30.710 --> 03:32.840
I'd be up at the rectory
with Father Maskell.

03:38.260 --> 03:40.140
Uh-uh. Is that it right there?

03:42.973 --> 03:44.853
Unbelievable. It's hard to recognize it.

03:49.688 --> 03:50.518
It's changed.

03:52.065 --> 03:54.395
Didn't change much.
If I had to bet the farm on it,

03:54.484 --> 03:57.324
I'd say that was his office right there,
because I dashed up.

03:57.404 --> 03:58.704
[Charles makes whooshing sound]

04:00.240 --> 04:02.950
-[man] Is that where the abuse happened?
-Yes, yes, yes.

04:07.914 --> 04:10.754
<i>Father Maskell taught me</i>
<i>how to drink and forget problems.</i>

04:11.626 --> 04:14.336
<i>Father Maskell taught me</i>
<i>how to, uh, take a drug</i>

04:14.755 --> 04:17.915
<i>if, uh, I wanted to forget</i>
<i>about what was happening around me.</i>

04:20.969 --> 04:24.769
The first wine I drank
was out of a chalice.

04:25.932 --> 04:28.692
Okay. And he said, "I have wine
that's left over from Mass,

04:28.769 --> 04:30.479
can you take care of it for me?"

04:33.940 --> 04:35.690
Because, you know, I was altar boy.

04:36.109 --> 04:38.449
That's where it--
That's how it all started.

04:39.946 --> 04:41.276
<i>I knew the young Maskell.</i>

04:42.616 --> 04:46.576
<i>And as he got older,</i>
<i>he got meaner, dirtier, and more evil.</i>

04:48.497 --> 04:52.957
So, if we get anything
out of this conversation today, okay...

04:54.753 --> 04:56.763
if the Catholic Church...

04:58.006 --> 05:01.586
would have dealt
with this properly back in '67,

05:02.177 --> 05:03.507
<i>and they knew about it...</i>

05:04.763 --> 05:06.523
<i>there would have been no murder.</i>

05:10.060 --> 05:11.230
We-- We wouldn't be here.

06:24.050 --> 06:25.140
There you are.

06:25.802 --> 06:28.052
-There's a Cesnik if I ever met one.
-Gerry.

06:28.138 --> 06:29.348
Nice to see you.

06:29.764 --> 06:30.934
-How are you?
-Fine.

06:31.766 --> 06:32.806
-I know.
-I am now.

06:33.351 --> 06:34.731
[Marilyn] Thank you for coming.

06:34.978 --> 06:37.728
It just makes me wanna cry,
the two of you getting together.

06:37.814 --> 06:40.444
This just makes me wanna cry.

06:40.525 --> 06:42.105
We've been talking about the ring.

06:42.193 --> 06:44.453
-I'm wondering if-- Do you have it with--?
-[Marilyn] I do.

06:44.529 --> 06:46.569
Yeah. The ring that I gave Cathy.

06:48.074 --> 06:49.914
And I told them I could identify it.

06:59.836 --> 07:00.796
That's it.

07:01.212 --> 07:04.802
I have to tell you that that ring
was on Cathy the day she died.

07:05.634 --> 07:07.804
[Gerry] The inside is engraved in Greek.

07:09.095 --> 07:11.175
[speaking Greek]

07:14.851 --> 07:18.231
[in English]
Agape is the unconditional love,

07:18.313 --> 07:20.483
the characteristic supposedly
of Christians.

07:21.358 --> 07:22.858
That's what the ring says.

07:23.485 --> 07:26.815
[Marilyn] Learning all this about Cathy,
I didn't know any of this.

07:26.905 --> 07:30.195
I started going through my mother's things
and I found all this.

07:30.784 --> 07:31.914
Somebody murdered her.

07:32.702 --> 07:34.372
They need to investigate this.

07:34.454 --> 07:36.674
My visit to the police was not--

07:36.915 --> 07:38.665
Did not bring me any closure.

07:39.000 --> 07:41.130
It opened up more questions to me.

07:44.798 --> 07:48.718
<i>It was August 1969,</i>
<i>she came home to Pittsburgh.</i>

07:52.055 --> 07:55.925
<i>She wanted to explain</i>
<i>why she was leaving Keough</i>

07:56.017 --> 07:59.267
<i>to those that she cared about</i>
<i>and those who cared about her.</i>

08:02.190 --> 08:05.240
<i>When Cathy came home,</i>
<i>it was always so happy,</i>

08:05.318 --> 08:08.528
and we would stay up all night
laughing and talking,

08:09.572 --> 08:12.332
<i>but she wasn't her happy-go-lucky self.</i>

08:13.576 --> 08:15.196
<i>She definitely was sad.</i>

08:15.996 --> 08:17.786
And at the time, I--

08:17.872 --> 08:22.092
I attributed some of this to the changes
that were going on in her life.

08:27.757 --> 08:32.047
Turns out, in the September
before she died, she came to see me.

08:33.138 --> 08:37.268
Because by then she found out
that they were declining the experiment,

08:37.976 --> 08:39.976
and that the order put her in--

08:40.395 --> 08:43.265
Well, you either go back
into the convent, or you leave.

08:43.773 --> 08:46.113
And I did know that she had
to give an answer by--

08:46.943 --> 08:48.153
By December 31st.

08:48.236 --> 08:52.816
So, at the time she died,
she had about six or seven more weeks

08:53.408 --> 08:56.198
in which to answer the ultimatum
that she was given.

08:57.162 --> 09:00.502
She said there's so much going on
in my mind now.

09:01.249 --> 09:02.919
I think the experiment...

09:04.461 --> 09:05.341
was here.

09:05.670 --> 09:07.760
-[Diane] Mm-hm.
-I think Gerry was here.

09:08.214 --> 09:10.384
And I think the abuse was here.

09:10.467 --> 09:12.047
Yeah. Yeah.

09:13.261 --> 09:16.141
[Marilyn] <i>She had been in the convent</i>
<i>for so long</i>

09:16.389 --> 09:19.729
<i>that my parents were concerned,</i>
<i>my dad especially,</i>

09:20.310 --> 09:24.270
<i>that she was gonna struggle</i>
<i>with living out in the world, you know.</i>

09:25.815 --> 09:28.735
<i>My dad said, "You don't pay bills.</i>

09:28.902 --> 09:31.742
<i>You don't get a paycheck in the convent.</i>

09:32.280 --> 09:35.780
<i>The world is a dangerous place</i>
<i>and you don't understand that."</i>

09:36.659 --> 09:39.909
<i>And she said, "How do you know</i>
<i>my world's not a dangerous place?</i>

09:42.749 --> 09:45.749
<i>How do you know there's not danger</i>
<i>in what I'm doing now?"</i>

09:47.962 --> 09:50.922
<i>I questioned it for a time frame,</i>
<i>and I kept thinking</i>

09:51.007 --> 09:54.797
<i>if she told me about the experiment,</i>
<i>she would've told me about the abuse,</i>

09:55.470 --> 09:59.930
but, um, the more I think about it now,
she would have never told me.

10:01.726 --> 10:03.556
<i>She was very protective of me,</i>

10:03.978 --> 10:07.518
<i>being her younger sister,</i>
<i>still being in college.</i>

10:10.318 --> 10:13.488
<i>And I can imagine</i>
<i>that heavy burden on her,</i>

10:14.322 --> 10:17.622
'cause Cathy never said
she was gonna do something she didn't do.

10:18.535 --> 10:21.155
If she told them
she was gonna make it stop, she--

10:21.246 --> 10:24.166
If that portion of all of this
is accurate...

10:25.416 --> 10:28.336
<i>all of these girls</i>
<i>can't all be telling a lie.</i>

10:30.088 --> 10:33.928
<i>Cathy would have been working</i>
<i>to make it stop, no doubt in my mind.</i>

10:37.303 --> 10:40.063
-Still-- It's still a great puzzle to me.
-[Diane] Yes.

10:40.140 --> 10:43.430
I mean, neither of us knew anything
about this abuse stuff.

10:43.518 --> 10:45.558
-This is the puzzle.
-As part of the context.

10:45.645 --> 10:47.105
-And Russell--
-Until 1994.

10:47.605 --> 10:49.395
-And what did Russell know?
-Russell.

10:55.989 --> 11:00.619
After Cathy died,
Russ just wanted to be separated

11:00.702 --> 11:04.502
from anything related to convent life,

11:04.581 --> 11:06.171
<i>related to Cathy.</i>

11:06.666 --> 11:07.956
<i>She wanted a new life.</i>

11:09.669 --> 11:16.219
<i>So, Russ left the convent, got married,</i>
<i>and had two children.</i>

11:18.845 --> 11:20.675
I sold her a house, actually.

11:21.055 --> 11:25.055
<i>She moved out here to Carroll County,</i>
<i>and we did a lot together.</i>

11:26.185 --> 11:30.225
<i>I had many conversations with her,</i>
<i>but it would never go in that direction,</i>

11:30.315 --> 11:31.645
she wouldn't allow it.

11:31.983 --> 11:33.993
And I would say, "What happened?

11:35.028 --> 11:36.858
<i>Do you know more than you're saying?</i>

11:37.405 --> 11:38.945
Why can't you talk about it?"

11:39.365 --> 11:42.735
And she'd say,
"My life is in a different place.

11:43.161 --> 11:45.831
That was my life before."
That's what she'd say.

11:46.080 --> 11:48.580
It was like, one day, she's gonna talk.

11:48.666 --> 11:50.076
One day, it's gonna come out.

11:56.549 --> 11:59.929
[Patricia]
<i>1997, I heard that she had cancer.</i>

12:00.595 --> 12:03.465
We stayed in touch.
I went to visit her in the hospital

12:03.556 --> 12:05.886
<i>when she had surgeries</i>
<i>and things like that.</i>

12:07.435 --> 12:11.605
<i>A couple years pass, and it's 2001.</i>

12:12.023 --> 12:15.493
You know, the stories are out
in papers and all that,

12:15.568 --> 12:17.858
and Maskell's name was being mentioned.

12:18.780 --> 12:20.740
<i>So, this friend of mine</i>

12:20.823 --> 12:23.793
<i>was working as a nurse</i>
<i>at Stella Maris hospice,</i>

12:24.452 --> 12:26.502
<i>and she calls me up and said,</i>

12:26.579 --> 12:30.629
"Pat, I want you to know
that Father Maskell died this afternoon.

12:32.752 --> 12:35.462
<i>But don't tell anybody,</i>
<i>I could lose my job."</i>

12:37.840 --> 12:41.470
<i>So, that evening, not listening</i>
<i>to my friend, I called Russ.</i>

12:41.552 --> 12:43.052
<i>That's the only person I called.</i>

12:43.137 --> 12:47.427
And I said, "Russ, I just want you to know
that Father Maskell died this afternoon."

12:47.934 --> 12:52.064
And Russ's one remark was,

12:52.355 --> 12:55.065
"Well, he went to his grave
with his secret."

12:58.361 --> 13:03.781
<i>Somehow, Russ did feel</i>
<i>that he was involved with Cathy's death.</i>

13:05.535 --> 13:08.495
And there was more to the story
than I knew.

13:09.330 --> 13:12.960
And then I get a phone call two days later
from her husband...

13:14.460 --> 13:15.840
<i>saying that Russ died.</i>

13:25.555 --> 13:29.095
Then we get some, um,
Saturday afternoon ice cream.

13:29.976 --> 13:31.226
-Yeah.
-[Jean] Mm-hm.

13:34.480 --> 13:36.690
I don't tell her
I put peanut butter right in it

13:36.774 --> 13:41.204
because this is more of the protein
that I want her to get,

13:41.863 --> 13:43.453
instead of just ice cream.

13:44.407 --> 13:45.577
I do the best I can.

13:45.658 --> 13:46.738
[laughing]

13:51.164 --> 13:53.884
<i>I was feeling feelings about my mom.</i>

13:54.542 --> 13:59.132
This feeling of that 16-year-old
behind that wall of lies,

13:59.213 --> 14:01.633
just saying, "Where were you?"

14:01.716 --> 14:03.966
You know, "Where were you?"

14:08.765 --> 14:12.885
<i>How she has been there for me</i>
<i>in so many ways,</i>

14:13.728 --> 14:19.938
<i>but how to let that be enough</i>
<i>when she wasn't there for me</i>

14:20.610 --> 14:21.900
when this was going on.

14:23.071 --> 14:27.331
<i>So, what I did what I asked Abbie if, um,</i>
<i>I wrote something, would she post it.</i>

14:32.538 --> 14:34.828
<i>"Hi, this is my first posting</i>

14:34.916 --> 14:37.166
on this wonderful grassroots
healing site.

14:38.294 --> 14:40.844
<i>As I care for my 88-year-old mother,</i>

14:41.130 --> 14:42.550
<i>I'm painfully aware</i>

14:42.799 --> 14:46.089
<i>of one of the many things robbed</i>
<i>from me by Joseph Maskell.</i>

14:47.053 --> 14:50.813
He took, deliberately and methodically,
my God-given right

14:50.890 --> 14:53.810
to a deep, trusting relationship
with my mom,

14:54.185 --> 14:56.145
and her right to be there for me."

14:58.147 --> 15:02.187
<i>The more that I am connecting</i>
<i>to the part of me</i>

15:02.276 --> 15:05.406
that survived after Cathy...

15:06.114 --> 15:08.534
um... the more I'm beginning to--

15:08.825 --> 15:10.535
To touch the anger.

15:10.618 --> 15:14.788
The anger pushes you forward
and you start talking to people,

15:14.872 --> 15:17.332
and being in front of a camera,
and you know--

15:17.500 --> 15:22.090
You start to do things
that put your feelings and thoughts

15:22.171 --> 15:26.181
out there for others to critique,
you know.

15:27.718 --> 15:29.758
[Abbie] <i>When I look back now</i>

15:29.846 --> 15:32.346
<i>at all the different personalities</i>
<i>that we've met,</i>

15:32.432 --> 15:38.402
Jean stands out as someone
who has consistently told

15:38.479 --> 15:42.569
<i>the same story, and has, sort of,</i>
<i>a sense of personal integrity.</i>

15:43.317 --> 15:48.527
She's taking her own insights
and the implications of all this,

15:48.865 --> 15:51.235
and trying to put the pieces together.

15:51.325 --> 15:55.785
But she's probably not willing
to be definite about it

15:55.872 --> 15:57.832
until she's absolutely sure.

16:04.881 --> 16:08.381
[Jean] <i>Brother Bob is still,</i>
<i>to this day, faceless to me.</i>

16:11.888 --> 16:15.808
<i>But my memory is beginning</i>
<i>to flesh out more and more.</i>

16:19.979 --> 16:24.029
<i>Brother Bob said to me</i>
<i>that he knew Cathy Cesnik</i>

16:24.484 --> 16:28.534
<i>and that, um, she was confiding in him</i>

16:28.613 --> 16:31.073
<i>that she was going to the police</i>
<i>about the abuse.</i>

16:33.409 --> 16:36.159
And he hit her,
he didn't mean to kill her.

16:38.539 --> 16:41.079
<i>On top of repressing the memories,</i>

16:41.959 --> 16:44.749
<i>the experience was so traumatizing</i>

16:45.004 --> 16:48.974
<i>that it's pushed a lot of the identity</i>
<i>of this person--</i>

16:49.050 --> 16:53.180
Any facial identity,
that has not surfaced.

16:57.975 --> 17:01.935
<i>I do remember that he had markings</i>
<i>on his abdomen.</i>

17:02.897 --> 17:06.857
It was a birthmark or it was a mole
of some sort, right over on this side.

17:07.443 --> 17:12.532
And he had a small incision
on the right side of his abdomen.

17:20.164 --> 17:24.594
<i>I understand that people are going</i>
<i>to wanna see if this one person,</i>

17:24.669 --> 17:26.919
me, who remembers what I remember,

17:27.505 --> 17:31.375
can't remember a little more
to get a little clearer,

17:33.094 --> 17:36.514
<i>to get more of an identity</i>
<i>to who that Brother Bob is.</i>

17:44.063 --> 17:47.233
<i>But I can't force myself</i>
<i>to remember anything else,</i>

17:47.316 --> 17:51.646
<i>and in all honesty, I don't know</i>
<i>when and if that is surfacing.</i>

17:59.453 --> 18:01.913
[Marilyn] Well, let me, um--
Just a little, Bob.

18:02.415 --> 18:03.455
That's good for me.

18:04.083 --> 18:06.003
I'll bet I can get it on my phone.

18:06.085 --> 18:07.625
Yeah, I got it on my phone.

18:09.714 --> 18:14.144
<i>When Cathy went missing, Russell told me--</i>
<i>She said, "Cathy went shopping</i>

18:14.218 --> 18:16.428
<i>to get you something</i>
<i>for your engagement."</i>

18:17.305 --> 18:20.215
I thought, oh, my gosh,
if we hadn't gotten engaged, you know--

18:20.308 --> 18:22.388
You know how you think that?
If I hadn't gotten engaged,

18:22.476 --> 18:25.186
she wouldn't have gone shopping,
and she wouldn't have been

18:25.271 --> 18:28.071
in the wrong place at the wrong time.
You know, which--

18:28.232 --> 18:30.282
The wrong-place-wrong-time story again.

18:33.321 --> 18:36.161
<i>She left to go shopping.</i>
<i>Other than that, I knew nothing.</i>

18:37.491 --> 18:40.241
<i>So, I didn't know if she'd died</i>
<i>before she got to the store,</i>

18:40.328 --> 18:41.998
<i>or after the store, or anything.</i>

18:46.083 --> 18:49.803
[Childs] <i>The entire mall was checked</i>
<i>by investigators from the city at the time</i>

18:49.879 --> 18:53.089
<i>in an attempt to locate a store</i>
<i>that she may have gone into.</i>

18:54.300 --> 18:55.640
There was no indication

18:55.926 --> 18:58.296
they were able to find
that she made this purchase.

18:58.387 --> 19:01.557
Now, she could've made
a cash purchase and, uh...

19:02.516 --> 19:04.226
they just weren't able to locate it,

19:04.310 --> 19:06.730
<i>but they never were able to make</i>
<i>that determination</i>

19:06.812 --> 19:09.732
<i>whether she actually, um,</i>
<i>made that purchase.</i>

19:13.861 --> 19:16.531
[Marilyn] I saw the necklace yesterday
for the first time.

19:16.614 --> 19:21.084
And, um, in looking at it,
the bell would symbolize a wedding,

19:21.160 --> 19:25.160
which makes sense, 'cause we had
just gotten engaged the week before.

19:26.290 --> 19:28.750
-Did you see this, Bob?
-Yeah. Let's see it.

19:31.712 --> 19:35.262
-Yeah, it does look like bell, doesn't it?
-[Jean] It does look like a bell.

19:35.341 --> 19:37.511
-It looks like it'd be appropriate.
-Yeah.

19:37.635 --> 19:39.635
And-- And your birthstone.

19:41.597 --> 19:44.597
So, I understand this birthstone
is a peridot

19:44.684 --> 19:47.404
<i>and that would be an August birthstone.</i>

19:48.145 --> 19:52.775
My husband's birthday is in August
so, it could've symbolized his birthday.

19:54.026 --> 19:57.446
<i>You have to understand,</i>
<i>Cathy was very, very happy for me</i>

19:57.780 --> 19:59.200
<i>that I chose Bob.</i>

20:00.700 --> 20:03.120
<i>She really thought Bob</i>
<i>would take care of me forever,</i>

20:03.202 --> 20:07.292
<i>and as a matter of fact, um,</i>
<i>Bob had gone to Vietnam for a year</i>

20:07.373 --> 20:08.833
<i>and my sister wrote to him,</i>

20:09.125 --> 20:12.035
<i>because she was trying to establish</i>
<i>a relationship with him.</i>

20:14.004 --> 20:17.304
<i>If this is true,</i>
<i>this would be so typical Cathy,</i>

20:17.508 --> 20:20.928
<i>because everything she did had a meaning</i>
<i>and everything was deep.</i>

20:21.470 --> 20:24.100
So, that would've been Cathy.

20:24.932 --> 20:25.932
Totally.

20:40.239 --> 20:42.119
[man speaking indistinctly on TV]

20:52.042 --> 20:55.502
[man] Um, Edgar, I wanted to show you
these pictures.

20:58.591 --> 21:00.221
You can flip through them.

21:03.512 --> 21:05.852
Does that look familiar to you at all?

21:05.931 --> 21:07.271
No.

21:12.104 --> 21:13.694
That's jewelry or something.

21:14.190 --> 21:15.070
[man] Mm-hm.

21:16.233 --> 21:20.283
It's a necklace that you gave
to your first wife for Christmas.

21:21.197 --> 21:22.947
Do you remember giving that to her?

21:23.866 --> 21:26.576
Her birthstone was red.

21:30.706 --> 21:34.246
So, why would you have gotten her
a green birthstone, which is August?

21:37.588 --> 21:39.548
I don't have the slightest idea.

21:41.759 --> 21:45.509
We know Sister Cathy was out buying
a present for her sister.

21:46.263 --> 21:51.523
And that, a month later,
you gave this necklace to your wife.

21:55.231 --> 21:57.441
Did you show it to Cathy's sister?

21:57.525 --> 22:02.605
Yeah, and Cathy's sister is wondering
whether that might be her necklace,

22:02.988 --> 22:06.528
uh, because she knows her sister was out
buying her an engagement present

22:06.617 --> 22:09.037
that night, and as you see
in that necklace,

22:09.328 --> 22:10.788
it has a wedding bell...

22:11.747 --> 22:14.997
it has a birthstone
that is the same birthstone

22:15.084 --> 22:18.754
as the man that Sister Cathy's sister
was marrying.

22:19.505 --> 22:22.505
So, she thinks there might be
some significance to that necklace,

22:22.591 --> 22:25.091
and she's wondering
whether you might have gotten it

22:25.177 --> 22:27.347
from Sister Cathy that night.

22:37.231 --> 22:39.281
[sighs]

22:42.278 --> 22:44.028
Means nothing to me.

22:45.990 --> 22:48.120
Did you encounter Sister Cathy that night?

22:48.742 --> 22:49.662
No.

22:50.619 --> 22:53.159
Now, if people think that
that was the necklace

22:53.247 --> 22:55.917
that Sister Cathy bought the night
she disappeared,

22:56.542 --> 22:58.632
and you gave it to your first wife,

22:58.711 --> 23:01.801
do you understand why people
are suspicious because of that?

23:02.298 --> 23:03.258
Mm-hm. [grunts]

23:13.350 --> 23:14.810
[Childs]
<i>There is a police report indicating</i>

23:14.893 --> 23:17.813
<i>that when, uh, Sister Cesnik went missing,</i>

23:18.230 --> 23:21.690
<i>we have an eyewitness</i>
<i>that saw a male driver</i>

23:21.775 --> 23:24.145
<i>driving Sister Cesnik's vehicle</i>
<i>from the scene.</i>

23:25.154 --> 23:28.994
<i>It appeared as though Sister Cesnik</i>
<i>was trying to exit the vehicle</i>

23:29.074 --> 23:32.544
on the passenger side,
but she never got out of the vehicle.

23:33.954 --> 23:38.464
<i>At the time the vehicle was recovered,</i>
<i>there was mud on the tires...</i>

23:38.542 --> 23:40.712
<i>there was a branch inside the vehicle.</i>

23:41.754 --> 23:44.134
<i>It was a twig, a small branch,</i>

23:44.757 --> 23:48.177
<i>and it would be consistent with the area</i>
<i>where the body was found.</i>

23:48.636 --> 23:51.506
<i>So, the driver would've been</i>
<i>the one to drive</i>

23:51.972 --> 23:53.892
<i>from the area where the body</i>
<i>was located</i>

23:53.974 --> 23:56.524
<i>back where the Carriage House was located,</i>

23:57.186 --> 24:00.396
<i>because he would've been the last person</i>
<i>to operate the vehicle.</i>

24:00.814 --> 24:03.944
[man] This might be urban legend,
and I don't know if it's in the reports,

24:04.026 --> 24:06.646
but we've heard that, uh,
there was indication

24:06.737 --> 24:08.067
that perhaps someone who drove

24:08.155 --> 24:12.275
with both of their feet might have driven
the car at some point that night.

24:12.368 --> 24:14.368
Does that ring any bells with you?

24:16.830 --> 24:18.620
[Childs] After they located the vehicle,

24:18.707 --> 24:22.337
there was mud located, um,
on the brake pedal

24:22.419 --> 24:25.299
but no mud recovered from the gas pedal,

24:26.006 --> 24:28.836
which may have led investigators
to believe that the person

24:28.926 --> 24:35.096
that drove the vehicle, um, used two feet
to, uh, operate the vehicle.

24:38.102 --> 24:41.442
[man] I'm just curious if by any chance
you drive with both of your feet?

24:43.273 --> 24:45.443
What's that got to do with anything?

24:45.526 --> 24:49.526
I was just curious because whoever drove
Cathy's car that night,

24:49.613 --> 24:54.333
based on the mud on the pedal,
drove with two different feet.

24:55.285 --> 24:56.655
I don't drive at all.

24:57.746 --> 24:58.906
But back in the day?

24:59.707 --> 25:01.707
-Did you drive with two feet?
-Yeah.

25:07.965 --> 25:11.925
I had nothing to do with her
disappearance, her murder or anything.

25:17.391 --> 25:18.981
[man] What about other suspects?

25:20.269 --> 25:23.439
<i>We have talked to Edgar Davidson</i>
<i>quite a few times,</i>

25:23.522 --> 25:28.362
<i>and he admitted that he is the person</i>
<i>who called </i> The Jerry Turner Show

25:28.902 --> 25:33.452
<i>in the '70s to talk about evidence</i>
<i>about the murder of Sister Cathy.</i>

25:34.033 --> 25:37.493
Are you able to verify or confirm
whether he's ever been looked at?

25:38.203 --> 25:42.043
No. I can't comment on anything
we're looking at currently

25:42.124 --> 25:43.924
or any part of that investigation.

25:44.001 --> 25:47.501
Some of the things I've commented on
is because you knew about them already,

25:47.588 --> 25:48.668
and I can comment.

25:49.423 --> 25:53.143
Then the other one is a neighbor
of Sister Cathy's named Billy Schmidt,

25:53.594 --> 25:55.144
<i>whose family we're working with,</i>

25:55.220 --> 25:59.850
<i>and they are, for various reasons,</i>
<i>convinced that their family member, Billy,</i>

25:59.933 --> 26:02.273
<i>who lived across the hall from her,</i>
<i>was involved.</i>

26:04.062 --> 26:07.362
As far as viable suspects,
current suspects,

26:07.816 --> 26:10.986
I can't say anything
regarding what we're doing

26:11.069 --> 26:12.399
or what we know about that.

26:13.947 --> 26:14.947
[dogs barking]

26:15.824 --> 26:19.544
[Barbara] <i>I told detectives about it</i>
<i>that came to see me in the '90s.</i>

26:20.287 --> 26:22.997
They were reopening the case.

26:23.707 --> 26:26.997
<i>And I've told them everything that I know</i>
<i>about it just like I'm telling you.</i>

26:28.170 --> 26:29.460
<i>I did ask them...</i>

26:30.672 --> 26:34.932
"I know you didn't have DNA back then,
but I know you have DNA today.

26:36.136 --> 26:39.426
Did you find any cigarette butts
back there where her body was found?

26:40.516 --> 26:41.846
<i>Maybe Salem?"</i>

26:42.601 --> 26:46.651
I told them Bill smoked Salem,
and they looked at each other,

26:47.731 --> 26:51.531
and the one said,
"Yeah, we did find some cigarette butts."

26:52.528 --> 26:54.398
<i>But I never heard how it turned out.</i>

26:55.989 --> 26:57.369
Well...

26:59.076 --> 27:02.576
We-- I can't tell you what,
but we have a piece of evidence

27:02.788 --> 27:05.668
that was recovered
that we did develop DNA from.

27:06.708 --> 27:08.288
[man 1] And is that piece of evidence--?

27:08.377 --> 27:10.457
Is that the cigarette
that I've heard about?

27:13.131 --> 27:14.011
[laughing]

27:14.132 --> 27:15.182
-Yeah.
-[man 2] Yes.

27:15.259 --> 27:20.009
Okay. And would that cigarette
most likely be linked to the crime?

27:24.142 --> 27:25.232
It could be.

27:25.310 --> 27:27.400
The reason we didn't really
wanna mention that

27:27.479 --> 27:29.979
is because we're still--
It's still open investigation,

27:30.065 --> 27:32.315
we still got a couple people
we wanna look at.

27:32.401 --> 27:33.941
Okay? Um...

27:34.903 --> 27:37.823
Let's just say this,
all the things you've commented on

27:38.365 --> 27:39.905
are all very interesting to me.

27:41.493 --> 27:43.663
And all of those things
will be re-looked at.

27:44.288 --> 27:48.958
Any person in the past that was looked at,
polygraphed, brought in for interviews,

27:49.793 --> 27:54.763
<i>Koob, McKeon, Maskell,</i>
<i>several other civilians...</i>

27:55.424 --> 27:58.144
<i>We are gonna revisit</i>
<i>a lot of these things.</i>

27:58.719 --> 28:02.259
And I do have hope that one day,
we solve this case.

28:12.399 --> 28:13.229
[Abbie] Uh...

28:14.484 --> 28:17.864
So, this is-- Yeah,
these are the Malecki papers,

28:17.946 --> 28:19.656
the old newspaper articles.

28:21.325 --> 28:23.575
<i>Four days after Sister Cathy was abducted,</i>

28:23.660 --> 28:29.040
<i>a young woman named Joyce Malecki</i>
<i>was abducted and murdered.</i>

28:30.751 --> 28:32.921
[Tom] <i>"Understandably,</i>
<i>police investigators</i>

28:33.003 --> 28:35.593
<i>and newspaper reporters</i>
<i>were intensely interested</i>

28:35.672 --> 28:39.262
<i>in the possibility that there might be</i>
<i>some connection between the two killings,</i>

28:40.135 --> 28:43.005
but no such link between the murders
has ever been established,

28:43.096 --> 28:46.676
according to FBI
and Baltimore Police officials today."

28:49.061 --> 28:50.561
Growing up at a young age,

28:50.729 --> 28:53.649
we went to St. Clement's
Catholic Church

28:53.732 --> 28:55.282
and we went to Sunday school.

28:56.193 --> 29:00.743
<i>We would walk down to St. Clement's,</i>
<i>we'd go past 1st Avenue</i>

29:00.822 --> 29:04.992
<i>and that was the rectory</i>
<i>where Father Maskell lived.</i>

29:07.913 --> 29:09.333
[Tom] <i>She was his parishioner.</i>

29:09.414 --> 29:11.254
<i>The Maleckis lived two blocks</i>

29:11.333 --> 29:14.753
<i>from the rectory and church</i>
<i>where Maskell was.</i>

29:16.672 --> 29:18.802
[Darryl]
<i>We knew that the rectory was there.</i>

29:18.882 --> 29:21.302
<i>We knew Father Maskell was living there,</i>

29:21.843 --> 29:25.513
<i>and you would actually feel honored</i>
<i>being of the Catholic religion</i>

29:25.597 --> 29:27.927
to be that close to a priest.

29:30.269 --> 29:32.599
[Pat]
<i>The priest that they were investigating</i>

29:32.688 --> 29:34.608
<i>for Sister Catherine Cesnik's death,</i>

29:35.232 --> 29:36.192
<i>Priest Maskell,</i>

29:37.192 --> 29:42.412
sent my mother a sympathy card
when Joyce had her funeral.

29:44.408 --> 29:47.408
[Tom]
<i>No one, said the wise men of the FBI,</i>

29:47.494 --> 29:50.624
has ever made a connection
between Maskell and Malecki.

29:52.499 --> 29:58.549
Here's the card signed by Father Maskell
after Joyce Malecki is killed.

29:58.630 --> 30:00.300
She was two blocks from the rectory,

30:00.382 --> 30:03.932
she was going to Mass and confession,
and all the rest with Maskell,

30:04.303 --> 30:09.223
and, uh, if the FBI and its 4000 pages
of stuff doesn't have this, I'd--

30:09.308 --> 30:12.388
I'd feel even more disappointed in them
than I already am.

30:14.062 --> 30:17.982
[Abbie] <i>FBI had jurisdictions over</i>
<i>Joyce's death because her body was found</i>

30:18.066 --> 30:20.986
<i>in a wooded area</i>
<i>at Fort Meade Military Base.</i>

30:22.487 --> 30:25.027
<i>Tom Nugent had looked into it years ago,</i>

30:25.115 --> 30:28.035
<i>and he was told by the FBI</i>
<i>that they determined</i>

30:28.118 --> 30:31.658
<i>it didn't have anything to do with the,</i>
<i>you know, military or the government</i>

30:31.955 --> 30:33.955
<i>and so they didn't do an investigation.</i>

30:34.041 --> 30:36.461
<i>They had handed the case over</i>
<i>to Anne Arundel County.</i>

30:38.086 --> 30:42.966
<i>Anne Arundel County Police said,</i>
<i>"FBI never handed anything to us.</i>

30:43.050 --> 30:46.050
<i>We have no records, no case.</i>
<i>We never investigated anything."</i>

30:49.806 --> 30:53.976
Which left us saying,
did anybody investigate her murder?

30:55.395 --> 30:58.685
I've been pursuing this
for the last 15 years.

31:00.192 --> 31:04.782
<i>Once a year, cold cases are reviewed,</i>
<i>but nothing's been done.</i>

31:05.614 --> 31:07.324
<i>And my question is why?</i>

31:08.867 --> 31:12.947
I mean, I go to bed at night or I wake up
in the morning, and it's on my mind.

31:14.539 --> 31:15.789
<i>You know, who did this?</i>

31:15.874 --> 31:17.174
<i>It doesn't go away.</i>

31:22.881 --> 31:27.341
[Abbie] <i>I filed a Freedom</i>
<i>of Information Act request with the FBI,</i>

31:28.178 --> 31:33.388
<i>who confirmed they had about 4,000 pages</i>
<i>of documents on Joyce.</i>

31:34.309 --> 31:37.149
<i>It's been awaiting assignment</i>
<i>to someone to review.</i>

31:38.522 --> 31:43.112
Okay. So, in-- This was September 5th
of 2014 I sent it in.

31:44.611 --> 31:48.411
<i>I began writing them a letter</i>
<i>every four to six weeks saying,</i>

31:48.490 --> 31:49.740
<i>"Could you please update me</i>

31:49.825 --> 31:53.195
in terms of an anticipated delivery
of the documents?"

31:56.748 --> 31:57.708
<i>I naively thought,</i>

31:57.791 --> 31:59.751
<i>"Well, in six weeks, we'll have this."</i>

32:00.836 --> 32:02.666
<i>"The FBI's FOIA program</i>

32:02.754 --> 32:05.884
<i>has identified potential response</i>
<i>of information for your request</i>

32:06.341 --> 32:09.091
<i>and awaits assignment</i>
<i>to a government information specialist</i>

32:09.177 --> 32:10.427
<i>for further processing."</i>

32:13.181 --> 32:18.191
This one's from January 2015, so,
five months or so after we sent it.

32:18.687 --> 32:21.437
"Currently, your request
is in the perfected backlog

32:21.898 --> 32:24.358
where your request is awaiting
assignment to an analyst."

32:25.235 --> 32:27.275
<i>There's a requirement on the federal law,</i>

32:27.362 --> 32:30.032
<i>how long an agency has to reply</i>
<i>to your request,</i>

32:30.615 --> 32:32.825
but there is no law

32:32.909 --> 32:36.709
about how long they have
to actually send you the documents.

32:37.622 --> 32:39.122
[Don] <i>When it first happened,</i>

32:39.207 --> 32:40.627
<i>the FBI told us</i>

32:40.709 --> 32:43.209
<i>that they did find fingerprints</i>
<i>in the car,</i>

32:44.171 --> 32:46.341
but they said they didn't have a name
to attach it to.

32:46.923 --> 32:49.343
<i>They also said they had forensic evidence</i>

32:50.051 --> 32:53.051
<i>from her nails, where she apparently</i>
<i>put up a fight,</i>

32:53.138 --> 32:55.138
<i>but they didn't have anything to go on.</i>

32:55.640 --> 33:00.100
<i>And that was one of the questions I asked</i>
<i>about 15 years ago,</i>

33:01.438 --> 33:03.268
"If you've got fingerprints,

33:03.356 --> 33:06.486
have you run them through
the National Data Bank?"

33:07.110 --> 33:08.240
And they said no.

33:08.820 --> 33:13.280
I said, "Well, if you got forensic
evidence, have you done any DNA on it?"

33:13.700 --> 33:15.620
They said, "No." I asked, why?

33:16.203 --> 33:19.213
They said, "Two reasons,
budget and manpower."

33:20.123 --> 33:22.083
<i>And that's the excuse I was given,</i>

33:22.167 --> 33:23.497
<i>and led out the door.</i>

33:25.670 --> 33:27.630
[Abbie] <i>"Dear FOIA Officer,</i>
<i>this is a request</i>

33:27.714 --> 33:29.554
<i>under the Freedom of Information Act."</i>

33:31.259 --> 33:35.099
<i>This one is dated February 2016.</i>

33:35.805 --> 33:39.555
<i>"Thank you for your inquiry regarding</i>
<i>the status of your FOIA request.</i>

33:39.643 --> 33:44.063
The current estimated date of completion
for your request is April 2016."

33:45.899 --> 33:47.149
<i>Weeks went by.</i>

33:48.443 --> 33:50.863
<i>April came and went</i>
<i>and I never heard anything.</i>

33:52.906 --> 33:56.446
<i>I filed the original request</i>
<i>in August of 2014.</i>

33:56.535 --> 33:59.825
-Coming in two and a half years.
-Seems like a hundred years ago.

33:59.913 --> 34:03.333
[Abbie] <i>And two and a half years</i>
<i>and we have nothing.</i>

34:06.169 --> 34:09.589
<i>-The Maleckis feel like--</i>
-[Gemma] <i>They've been abandoned.</i>

34:10.172 --> 34:11.013
[Abbie] <i>Yeah.</i>

34:15.679 --> 34:19.018
[Darryl] <i>Our sister Joyce</i>
<i>was 20 years old,</i>

34:19.099 --> 34:21.018
<i>in the prime of her life,</i>

34:21.101 --> 34:23.650
<i>and her life</i>
<i>being snatched away from her,</i>

34:24.103 --> 34:26.774
<i>it's a crime and it needs</i>
<i>to be dealt with accordingly.</i>

34:27.940 --> 34:30.281
My parents have passed away,

34:30.360 --> 34:33.699
everybody is going to pass away
at some point in time.

34:33.780 --> 34:39.540
And when we pass away, then, they won't
have to hear from anybody ever again.

34:39.619 --> 34:42.869
They can put it in their cold case file

34:42.956 --> 34:44.616
and forget about it.

34:44.708 --> 34:45.958
Somebody should talk to us.

34:46.585 --> 34:49.085
If there's nothing, tell us that.

34:50.255 --> 34:54.465
<i>Just don't put us in a closet</i>
<i>and hope we go away one day.</i>

35:24.914 --> 35:26.584
[C.T.] <i>Thank you, Mr. Chair,</i>
<i>Madam Vice-Chair,</i>

35:26.666 --> 35:28.036
<i>members of the committee.</i>

35:29.294 --> 35:33.554
<i>This bill was, uh-- Been back and forth</i>
<i>in front of this body since about 2003.</i>

35:33.632 --> 35:34.472
For some reason,

35:34.549 --> 35:37.839
this bill has been interpreted to be
an attack on religious organizations

35:38.553 --> 35:40.433
and it's died repeatedly.

35:55.820 --> 35:58.030
People would ask, you know,
25 years, you know,

35:58.698 --> 36:00.198
they're grown people, right?

36:00.283 --> 36:04.293
I was in combat, I was out of military by
the time I was 25, I'd served eight years.

36:06.956 --> 36:09.536
Well, the problem
with this is suppression.

36:09.626 --> 36:12.086
People don't wanna acknowledge
that it happened.

36:12.170 --> 36:15.760
<i>You've learned to live with the lie</i>
<i>as a child, so you can live as an adult.</i>

36:17.884 --> 36:20.304
<i>Growing up, I was in foster homes</i>

36:20.387 --> 36:22.137
<i>and I was adopted at some point</i>

36:22.514 --> 36:23.774
<i>by Tom and Millie Wilson.</i>

36:25.058 --> 36:25.888
He was a, uh--

36:26.393 --> 36:29.193
He was a school teacher, you know,
a Sunday school teacher,

36:29.270 --> 36:31.230
a Cub Scout leader,
and he was a pedophile.

36:31.564 --> 36:35.494
And so from, like, the ages
of eight or nine until about 16,

36:36.027 --> 36:37.397
I endured a lot.

36:39.239 --> 36:42.159
[Teresa] <i>Why do we wait so long</i>
<i>to come forward?</i>

36:42.826 --> 36:45.196
I was 40 years old when I came forward.

